newsitem.title: THAILAND: Earthquake rocks northern Thailand, no damage.
newsitem.headline: Earthquake rocks northern Thailand, no damage.

text.p: A medium-sized earthquake measuring 5.5 on the Richter scale hit northern Thailand early on Sunday but there were no reports of injuries or damage, a meteorological department official said.
The epicentre of the earthquake, which occurred at 00.51 a.m (1751 GMT) was about 225 kilometres (140 miles) northeast of Chiang Mai near the forested Thailand-Laos border, he told Reuters.
Tremors were felt in the cities of Chiang Mai and Chiang Rai, he said.
